# Mosquitto topic ACL — STAGED for the auth cutover (NOT yet active; see provisioning/broker-auth-cutover.md).
# Enforces ADR-0001/ADR-0010: only the dictator may publish any command topic; a node may publish only
# its own telemetry and subscribe only its own command topic. Load via acl_file in mosquitto-auth.conf.

# ── dictator: the server (PEP issuer + ingestion services + admin tools) ──
user dictator
topic readwrite #

# ── edge node c6-bench: telemetry up, only its own cmd down ──
# May NOT publish to any …/cmd (cannot command itself or any device).
user c6-bench
topic write home/edge/c6-bench/status
topic write home/edge/c6-bench/log
topic write home/edge/c6-bench/+/adv
topic write home/edge/c6-bench/+/history
topic write home/edge/c6-bench/+/reply
topic read  home/edge/c6-bench/cmd

# ── template for future actuator nodes (state up + ack up, only own cmd down) ──
# user <node-id>
# topic write home/<area>/<device_id>/state
# topic write home/<area>/<device_id>/cmd/ack
# topic read  home/<area>/<device_id>/cmd
